  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as financial transactions intended to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's source\n3. Integration: Making illegally obtained funds appear legitimate\n\nCommon methods include:\n- Cash deposits\n- Bank transfers\n- Investment schemes\n- Real estate purchases\n- Cryptocurrency transactions\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most countries criminalize intentional efforts to hide the source of funds from illegal activities like:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Organized crime\n- Corruption\n- Terrorism financing\n\nLegal penalties can include substantial fines and imprisonment.",
